"The memo gate caches node outputs so that **identical inputs \u2192 same result without recomputation**. Before running a node, the scheduler computes a content-aware signature (type, config, version, and each specific input port\u2019s content hash), checks the store for a previous result, and if found **reuses it (skip)** instead of executing the node again. This makes \u201cre-run only what changed\u201d and \u201cresume from a previous run\u201d the same mechanism\u2014even across process restarts, because the memo lives in the persistent store.\n\n**File:** `runtime/scheduler.py` (the `run` function and `_memo_sig` helper).  \nKey lines:\n```python\ncached = store.memo_get(sig)\nif nid not in force and cached and store.exists(cached):   # MEMO GATE\n    cas = cached\n    agent = f\"{ex.type}@memo\"\n    skipped.add(nid)\nelse:\n    cas = store.put_content(mod.run(inputs, ex.config))\n    store.memo_set(sig, cas)\n    ...\n```"